Responsibilities:-

1) Analyze, create automation plans 
2) Create and execute automated tests, track defects and report results 
3) Actively acquire information from stakeholders rather than relying entirely on written Specs 
4) Actively participate in inception, daily stand-ups and retrospective meeting &amp; represent testing 
5) Work effectively to define testable user stories, acceptance criteria, with all stakeholders 
6) Respond to change quickly, including changing, adding, or enhancing test scripts 
7) Automate the testing in-sprint and during SIT/UAT.
8) Manage Test data to be used for Test Automation 
9) Ensure continuous integration for testing code and implement continuous testing 
10) Risk and Issue Management - Identify, mitigate and escalate testing risks and issues 
11) Responsible for the timely delivery and utilization of automated scripts 
12) Accurately evaluate and report test results, test progress, and product quality

Requirements:-

1) Expert in UI test automation tools (Selenium WebDriver and Appium )
2)Minimum 7+ year’s experience in Mobile native app automation testing and 4-year web application automation experience.
3)Must have hands on experience in both Android and iOS mobile app automation (Selenium with Appium ).
4) Must have experience using a broad range of test automation frameworks - Appium, Cucumber, JBehave, Junit.
5) Expert knowledge of continuous Integration (CI) and Continuous Testing (CT) to streamline QA processes (Git, Maven, Eclipse, Jenkins, or similar) 
6) Good experience with SDLC practices of Agile, Behavioral and Test-Driven Development ( Scrum, similar) 
7) Experience in the field of financial/banking applications testing and testing on complex environments including multiple interfacing systems.
8) Strong technical knowledge – able to code in one or more scripting language (Java Must)
9) Experience in test automation and developing automation frameworks from scratch 
10) Experience automating testing in multiple technologies – Mobile, Mainframe, web, SQL
11) Experience of using and implementing a variety of test tools, including tools for test management / planning, defect tracking, test automation, test data management 
12) Experience with Agile &amp; Testing Tools like JIRA, Confluence would be an advantage.
13) Experience in designing and implementing test automation based on BDD.
14) Experience of working on agile projects and deliveries
15)Experience in SQL is must.
16) Possess excellent verbal and written communication skills.
16) A Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science (or equivalent experience)
